channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.

transcription: {"text": "Before the war started, Ukraine was like Disneyland for single dudes. We were looking to date, you know, the ratio of men to women was always very favorable. The nightlife was insane. Obviously now, I'm sure things are radically different. I know a ton of Ukrainian women have left and gone to Warsaw, Germany, Berlin. It's like, I've got lots of clients in Berlin. I've got a few clients that are in Warsaw and, you know, they're running around talking to girls, doing their day game approaches, whatnot. And like most of the girls that they meet that they actually like are Ukrainian refugees. So I guess my question is, like, have you seen anything interesting about that? Like, you know, is there any sort of like dating scene? Do you think those girls will come back once the war is over? What do you think is going to go on from like a dating perspective? Look, at the beginning, a lot of people left. Right now, a lot of them came back. Still, the numbers are still crazy of people that stayed. But also at the same time, a lot of the guys here are just in the army, right? So so still the ratio of guys to girls is still, I think, the same, if not even more. There's more women. Oh, yeah.
